abstract: WASHINGTON, May 2 -- The Republican Senators have decided to join actively in the debate on the Philippine Civil Government bill. abstract: Intercollegiate golf will be the feature this week. abstract: BALTIMORE, May 5 -- The market to-day fell into one of mere perfunctory tending. Nobody would take hold of any group to give it a bullish turn. abstract: Racegoers at the Morris Park track yesterday put in an afternoon of tranquil enjoyment that contrasted pleasantly with the earlier days of the meeting. abstract: NEWPORT, R.I., May 7. -- The Tax Assessors to-day completed their assessment for the year and fixed the tax at the rate of $11.40 on each $1,000, last year's rate being $11 on $1,000. abstract: LONDON, May 12. -- The American polo team was beaten to-day by Rugby by 6 goals to 4. The contest was played on the Roehampton Club's field and was the second match in the Coronation Cup tournament series. R. L. Agassiz played instead of Foxhall Keene for the American team. abstract: PHILADELPHIA, May 12. -- It was a heavy and sluggish market in Philadelphia to-day, few stocks escaping without some mark of depression. At the outset the market wavered, but yielded when the weakness became pronounced in New York. Readings, Electric Storage Battery, and Consolidated Lake Superior were the sensitive spots, and subsequently the shading-off process percolated through the whole list, with the single exception of Union Traction, which was immovable.

abstract: Westchester defeated the Camden Country Club of South Carolina yesterday in the second polo game for the Country Club Cups played on the field of the Country Club of Westchester. abstract: Schoolboys of Horace Mann School held their annual track and field games on the South Field track of Columbia University yesterday afternoon. abstract: "Fe-fi-fo-fum, I smell the blood of an Englishmun." THEN there follows in that ancient child's rhyme the threat of the converting of the bones of the Englishman into some farinaceous compound. abstract: HAVANA, May 20 -- The natal day of the Republic of Cuba found Havana arrayed like a Queen to await the coming of her lord. abstract: Lakewood won the Westchester Polo Cup yesterday in a very one-sided game with the Rockaway Club on the field of the Country Club of Westchester. The pinners scored 13 1/2 goals while the Rockaway men got only 2 1/2. Each one-half goal for a foul. abstract: WASHINGTON, May 27. -- The conferrees of the two houses of Congress on the River and Harbor bill to-day reached a final agreement on that bill. The exact figures showing the aggregate result of their work have not been determined, but it can be stated that of the $9,500,000 appropriation added by the Senate only about $4,500,000 was retained, the provisions calling for the remaining $5,000,000 being disagreed to by the House conferrees.

abstract: HONOLULU, May 24, via San Francisco, May 30 -- The effects of the volcanic eruption at St. Pierre are supposed to have been felt here.
